To get the data presented on the step5.txt dataset I applied the following transformations to the original data:

- Lowered the cases of all of the variable names.
- Replaced the "f" and the "t" at the beginning of some variable names with a more descriptive string "frequency" and "time" respectively.
- Removed special characters like "-", ",", "(", ")" from variable names.
- Assigned the "subjectid" name to the subject identification variable of the train and test data.
- Assigned the "activity" name to the activity identification variable.
- Merged the test activity data with the activity only table.
- Merged the train activity data with the activity only table.
- Merged the test data with the test subject data and the activity data.
- Merged the train data with the train subject data and the activity data.
- United the test data with the train data.
- Extracted only the mean and standard deviation measurements along with the subjectid and activity variables.
- Changed the subjectid from integer class to factor class.
- Changed the activity variable from string class to factor class.
- From the extracted data, created the step5 dataset with the calculation of the average of each variable for each subject and each activity.

